- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new Physics-Informed Neural Network (PINN) method for solving time-dependent stochastic partial differential equations (SPDEs) by incorporating the dynamically orthogonal (DO) and bi-orthogonal (BO) methods for representing stochastic processes. The PINN method is a type of machine learning method that combines neural networks with physical laws or constraints. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper addresses the problem of long-time integration of nonlinear SPDEs and proposes a numerical method based on PINNs and DO/BO methods. The paper also presents several numerical examples to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method. 
- cs.SI (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the problem of uncertainty propagation in physical systems modeled by SPDEs, and proposes a method based on PINNs and DO/BO methods to quantify the uncertainty.
